# Weekly release changelog

What's New shows **once per week** — on the first deploy after Monday. During the week, **append bullets** to the same week; do not show the overlay again until the next Monday week.

Before pushing to preview or `main`:

1. Edit [`src/lib/changelog.ts`](src/lib/changelog.ts):
   - **Same week (Tue–Sun):** append to `WEEKLY_CHANGELOG.items` only.
   - **First push after Monday:** set `weekStarts` to that Monday (`getCurrentReleaseWeekId()` / e.g. `22-06-2026`), new `title`, fresh `items` array.
   - Bump `APP_VERSION` and [`package.json`](package.json) `version` (semver) on each deploy.
2. Run `npm test` and `npm run build` (`verify-changelog` runs on prebuild).

Dates use **DD-MM-YYYY**. `weekStarts` must always be the Monday starting the current release week.

```ts
export const WEEKLY_CHANGELOG: WeeklyChangelog = {
  weekStarts: '22-06-2026', // Monday — update on first push after each Monday
  title: 'Short week summary',
  items: [
    'Existing bullet from earlier in the week',
    'New bullet added today',
  ],
}
export const APP_VERSION = '1.1.3' // match package.json
```
